Topic: Knowledge check

Link: https://www.theodinproject.com/lessons/foundations-git-basics

1. How do you create a new repository on GitHub?
- Click in the plus icon and select new repository.
- Add the name of the repository
- Add the REAME.md
- Press Create repository

2. How do you copy a repository onto your local machine from GitHub?
- First create the folder where you gonna clone the github repo and enter the folder.
- Copy the SSH link from the github repo.
- Open the terminal and type:
- git clone Add_the_SSH_link_from_github
- Enter the clone folder.

3. What is the default name of your remote connection?
origin / main

5. Explain what origin is in git push origin main.
origin denotes the remote repo where the project live.
git push origin main is the more specific way to push the changes to the remote server.

6. Explain what main is in git push origin main.
Is the name of the main branch or trunk.

7. Explain the two-stage system that Git uses to save files.
Is the stage area and commit repo.
The stage area is a waiting room, where all the modified files await to be commited to the repo.

8. How do you check the status of your current repository?
using the command: git status and git log

9. How do you add files to the staging area in git?
using the commmand: git add nameOfTheFile

10. How do you commit the files in the staging area and add a descriptive message?
git commit -m "atomicMessage"

11. How do you push your changes to your repository on GitHub?
if there is only one branch and is not another remote repo:
git push

12. How do you look at the history of your previous commits?
using the command: git log